# Packages installed by modules/60-dev-tools.sh.
# One apt package name per line. Lines starting with # (and blank lines) are
# ignored. This is the "add stuff here as you go" extension point for dev
# tooling — add a package name, commit, and re-run install.sh to pick it up.
# Nothing here is pentest-specific; keep it that way.
#
# Unlike the effective_kali branch, these all need to be listed explicitly:
# there's no pimpmykali-equivalent doing a bunch of installs for free on
# Pop!_OS, and git/curl/build-essential are confirmed NOT preinstalled on
# a stock Pop!_OS 22.04 desktop install.

git
curl
build-essential
tmux
jq
unzip
